President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Brian McGuire of New York as Deputy Under Secretary of the Treasury for Legislative Affairs and Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for Legislative Affairs. McGuire currently serves as Counselor to the Secretary of the Treasury for Legislative Affairs and has a background in law, government consulting, and journalism. He earned his B.A. from St. John's College and an M.A. in Philosophy from the University of Dallas.

Additionally, President Trump intends to nominate Chad Wolf of Virginia as the Under Secretary of Homeland Security for Strategy, Policy, and Plans. Wolf currently serves as Chief of Staff at the Department of Homeland Security and has previous experience as Acting Chief of Staff and Deputy Chief of Staff. He also served as Chief of Staff at the Transportation Security Administration and has a background in public policy consultancy and government work. Wolf earned his B.A. in history from Southern Methodist University and a master certificate in government contract management from Villanova University.